## 4. Headline finding

> The Phase 2e E-resistance observed in pure_algebraic (2 / 5 canonical E-bins above null p95) is **a sampling artifact of the canonical x-uniform grid**. Under an E-uniform alternative grid that disturbs the linear `coord → base_operand` mapping while preserving domain, endpoints, count, and determinism, **the within-bin grammar collapses to the permutation null in every populated bin**. The grammar's apparent "structure beyond the marginal" came from how the canonical grid traversed E-space, not from the substrate's lattice traversal under pure-algebraic algebra.

The disambiguation answers the open question from Phase 2e cleanly. The user's "hypothesis 1" (sampling artifact) is supported; "hypothesis 2" (genuine sub-E primitive) is refuted at this jitter level.

